## SECTION 3: Step-by-Step Derivations, Trace Tables & C Implementations

### 3.1 Priority Queue — C Implementation (Sorted Array, Ascending Priority)

Below is the complete, KTU-examinable C program. Read it line-by-line; every pointer manipulation is annotated.

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#define MAX 50

int pq[MAX];       // Array to store elements
int pr[MAX];       // Parallel array to store priorities
int size = 0;      // Current number of elements

void insert(int data, int priority) {
    int i;
    if (size == MAX) {
        printf("Queue is Full\n");
        return;
    }
    // Step 1: Find correct position (ascending priority order)
    // Higher priority = LOWER numerical value of 'priority'
    for (i = size - 1; i >= 0 && pr[i] > priority; i--) {
        pq[i + 1] = pq[i];      // Shift data to the right
        pr[i + 1] = pr[i];      // Shift priority to the right
    }
    // Step 2: Place new element at the found position
    pq[i + 1] = data;
    pr[i + 1] = priority;
    size++;
    printf("Inserted: Data = %d, Priority = %d\n", data, priority);
}

int deleteHighestPriority() {
    if (size == 0) {
        printf("Queue is Empty\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int highest = pq[0];   // Sorted: highest priority is at index 0
    // Shift all elements to the left
    for (int i = 0; i < size - 1; i++) {
        pq[i] = pq[i + 1];
        pr[i] = pr[i + 1];
    }
    size--;
    return highest;
}

void display() {
    if (size == 0) {
        printf("Queue is Empty\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Data\tPriority\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
        printf("%d\t%d\n", pq[i], pr[i]);
    }
}

int main() {
    insert(10, 3);
    insert(20, 1);
    insert(30, 2);
    insert(40, 5);
    display();
    printf("Deleted highest priority: %d\n", deleteHighestPriority());
    display();
    return 0;
}
```

**Step-by-Step Trace Table for `insert(10,3), insert(20,1), insert(30,2), insert(40,5)`:**

| Step | Operation | Internal State (Data \| Priority) | Comment |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | `insert(10, 3)` | `10 \mid 3` | Size 0 → 1; placed at index 0 |
| 2 | `insert(20, 1)` | `20 \mid 1, 10 \mid 3` | Priority 1 < 3, so inserted at front; size = 2 |
| 3 | `insert(30, 2)` | `20 \mid 1, 30 \mid 2, 10 \mid 3` | Priority 2 < 3 but > 1; placed in middle; size = 3 |
| 4 | `insert(40, 5)` | `20 \mid 1, 30 \mid 2, 10 \mid 3, 40 \mid 5` | Priority 5 is highest, so appended; size = 4 |
| 5 | `deleteHighestPriority()` | `30 \mid 2, 10 \mid 3, 40 \mid 5` | Returns 20 (was at index 0); elements shifted left; size = 3 |

**Expected Output:**
```
