**Q1. [KTU University Exam - Dec 2023]**
**Define a Priority Queue. How does it differ from a regular queue?**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
A Priority Queue is an abstract data type (ADT) in which each element is assigned a priority value, and the element with the highest priority is served first, regardless of insertion order. *(1 mark)*

In a regular queue, the deletion policy is strictly **FIFO (First-In-First-Out)** — the oldest element is always removed first. *(1 mark)*

In contrast, a Priority Queue follows a **priority-based deletion policy** — the element with the highest priority (lowest numerical value, by convention) is removed first, irrespective of when it was inserted. *(1 mark)*

