**Q2. [KTU University Exam - May 2024]**
**What is a Deque? Mention its two restricted variants.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
A Deque (Double-Ended Queue) is a linear data structure that allows insertion and deletion of elements from both the front and the rear ends. *(1 mark)*

The two restricted variants are: *(1 mark)*

1. **Input-Restricted Deque** — insertion is allowed only at the rear end, but deletion is allowed from both ends. *(0.5 marks)*
2. **Output-Restricted Deque** — deletion is allowed only at the front end, but insertion is allowed at both ends. *(0.5 marks)*

