> 3. **Confusing Min-Heap and Max-Heap priority conventions.** If the question says "lowest numerical priority value is highest priority" (min-heap convention), then insertion sorts in *ascending* order. If the reverse is stated, sort in descending order. Failing to clarify this in your algorithm explanation costs 1 mark.
> 4. **Forgetting the modular decrement in `insertFront` for Deque.** When `front == 0` and a new element must be inserted at the front, you must set `front = N - 1`, not `front = -1`. *Loss: 1 mark.*
