## 2. Deep Theoretical Analysis & KTU High-Yield Formula Sheet

### 2.1 Core Operational Logic — Anatomy of Every Operation

Every linked list operation follows a universal three-phase pattern:

- **Phase 1 — Traversal**: Move a temporary pointer `temp` from `head` to the desired position using a `while` loop.
- **Phase 2 — Modification**: Update the `next` pointers of relevant nodes (rearrange the "hooks").
- **Phase 3 — Memory Management**: If deleting, call `free()` to release the deallocated node's memory back to the heap.

### 2.2 Time & Space Complexity Cheat Sheet (KTU High-Yield)

| Operation | Singly Linked List | Doubly Linked List | Circular Linked List |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Traversal (Display)** | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ |
| **Insertion at Beginning** | $O(1)$ | $O(1)$ | $O(1)$ |
| **Insertion at End** | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ | $O(1)$ (tail pointer) or $O(n)$ |
| **Insertion at Position** | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ |
| **Deletion at Beginning** | $O(1)$ | $O(1)$ | $O(1)$ |
| **Deletion at End** | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ | $O(1)$ (tail) or $O(n)$ |
| **Deletion at Position** | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ |
| **Search** | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ |
| **Reverse** | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ | $O(n)$ |
| **Space per Node** | **data + 1 pointer** | **data + 2 pointers** | **data + 1 pointer** |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Memory Formula (High-Yield for KTU):**
> $$\text{Total Memory} = n \times (\text{size\_of(data)} + \text{size\_of(pointer)})$$
> For an `int` linked list on a 64-bit system: $n \times (4 + 8) = 12n$ bytes.

### 2.3 Real-World Engineering Applications

- **Music Player**: Each song is a node; the "Next" button moves to the next song via the `next` pointer.
- **Browser History**: Doubly linked list — "Back" and "Forward" buttons use `prev` and `next` pointers.
- **Undo/Redo in Editors**: Doubly linked list of states.
- **Operating Systems Kernel**: Process scheduling uses circular linked lists to cycle through processes.
- **Polynomial Representation**: Each term is a node with `coefficient`, `exponent`, and `next`.
