**(b) Delete from End:**

```c
void deleteFromEnd(struct Node **head) {
    if (*head == NULL) {
        printf("List is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    if ((*head)->next == NULL) {   // Only one node
        free(*head);
        *head = NULL;
        return;
    }
    struct Node *temp = *head;
    while (temp->next->next != NULL) {
        temp = temp->next;         // Reach second-last node
    }
    free(temp->next);              // Free the last node
    temp->next = NULL;             // Mark new end
}
```

**Diagram Explanation (for 7 marks):**

Before deletion: `HEAD → 10 → 20 → 30 → NULL`

After traversal, `temp` points to `20` (second-last). Then:
1. `free(temp->next)` → Node 30's memory is released.
2. `temp->next = NULL` → Node 20 becomes the new last node.

After deletion: `HEAD → 10 → 20 → NULL`

*(2 marks for function code + 3 marks for traversal logic + 2 marks for diagram/edge case handling)*

