**Model Solution:**

**(a) Doubly Linked List Structure:**

```c
struct DNode {
    int data;
    struct DNode *prev;
    struct DNode *next;
};
```

**Insert at Beginning (DLL):**

```c
void insertAtBeginningDLL(struct DNode **head, int value) {
    struct DNode *newNode = (struct DNode *)malloc(sizeof(struct DNode));
    newNode->data = value;
    newNode->prev = NULL;
    newNode->next = *head;
    if (*head != NULL) {
        (*head)->prev = newNode;   // Old first node points back
    }
    *head = newNode;               // Update head
}
```

**Delete from End (DLL):**

```c
void deleteFromEndDLL(struct DNode **head) {
    if (*head == NULL) return;
    struct DNode *temp = *head;
    while (temp->next != NULL) temp = temp->next;  // Reach last node
    if (temp->prev != NULL)
        temp->prev->next = NULL;   // Second-last becomes last
    else
        *head = NULL;              // Single node case
    free(temp);
}
```

*(1 mark structure + 3 marks insert + 3 marks delete)*

---

**(b) Reverse a Singly Linked List:**

```c
void reverse(struct Node **head) {
    struct Node *prev = NULL, *curr = *head, *next = NULL;
    while (curr != NULL) {
        next = curr->next;    // Save next
        curr->next = prev;    // Reverse the link
        prev = curr;          // Move prev forward
        curr = next;          // Move curr forward
    }
    *head = prev;             // New head
}
```

**Trace Table** for `10 → 20 → 30 → 40 → NULL`:

| Iteration | `prev` | `curr` | `next` | List State |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Initial | NULL | 10 | — | `10→20→30→40→NULL` |
| 1 | NULL | 10 | 20 | `10→NULL`, `20→30→40` |
| 2 | 10 | 20 | 30 | `20→10→NULL`, `30→40` |
| 3 | 20 | 30 | 40 | `30→20→10→NULL`, `40` |
| 4 | 30 | 40 | NULL | `40→30→20→10→NULL` |
| Exit | 40 | NULL | — | **New HEAD = 40** |

**Final Reversed List:** `40 → 30 → 20 → 10 → NULL`

*(3 marks code + 4 marks trace table/diagram)*

