### 🎯 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- ✅ A **node** = `data` + `next` pointer (SLL) or `data` + `prev` + `next` (DLL).
- ✅ **`head`** is the entry point; if `head == NULL`, the list is empty.
- ✅ **Always use `malloc()`** to create nodes and **`free()`** to deallocate deleted nodes.
- ✅ **Insertion at beginning** is the **fastest** operation — only $O(1)$.
- ✅ **Reversal** uses a three-pointer technique: `prev`, `curr`, `next`.
- ✅ **Circular LL** has no `NULL`; the last node points back to `head`.
- ✅ **DLL** allows traversal in both directions but uses **double the pointer memory**.
- ✅ **Time Complexity** for traversal/search in any linked list is $O(n)$.
- ✅ **Pass `head` by reference** (`Node **head`) when the function modifies the head pointer.
