### Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- [x] Stack = **LIFO**, Queue = **FIFO**.
- [x] Stack needs **1 pointer (`top`)**; Queue needs **2 pointers (`front`, `rear`)**.
- [x] All four core operations (`push`, `pop`, `enqueue`, `dequeue`) are **O(1)** in linked-list implementation.
- [x] `malloc` failure = **Overflow**; `top == NULL` / `front == NULL` = **Underflow**.
- [x] Always **save the pointer first, then update, then free** — never free and then dereference.
- [x] In a single-element queue, **both `front` and `rear` must become `NULL` together** after dequeue.
- [x] Display is always **O(n)** because it traverses the entire list.
- [x] Linked list solves the **fixed-size problem** of array stacks/queues but pays an **extra pointer per node** as memory overhead.
- [x] KTU exam weightage: This topic regularly appears as a **full 14-mark question** in Part B and as a **2–3 mark conceptual** in Part A.

