$$(4+6)x^5 + 2x^3 + (3+9)x^2 + 7 = 10x^5 + 2x^3 + 12x^2 + 7 \checkmark$$

## 3.5 Complexity Derivation

**Time Complexity Analysis:**

Let $m$ = number of terms in $P_1$ and $n$ = number of terms in $P_2$.

In the main `while` loop, in each iteration, **at least one** of the pointers (`p1` or `p2`) advances by one node. The loop terminates when **both** lists are exhausted.

$$\text{Maximum iterations} = m + n$$

Each iteration performs only $O(1)$ work (a few comparisons, an addition, a `malloc`). The two remaining `while` loops collectively add at most $m + n$ more iterations.

$$T(m, n) = O(m + n)$$

**Space Complexity Analysis:**

Every term in the result requires a new node. The result can have at most $m + n$ terms.

$$S(m, n) = O(m + n)$$

> [!NOTE]
> **Observation:** This is asymptotically optimal — you cannot do better than $O(m+n)$ time because you must read every input term at least once, and you cannot use less than $O(m+n)$ space because the output itself can be of that size.
