### 2.4 Real-World Engineering Applications of DLL

- **Browser History**: Back (`prev`) and Forward (`next`) buttons use exactly DLL logic.
- **Undo/Redo in Software**: Text editors store operations in DLLs so the cursor can move in both directions.
- **LRU Cache (Least Recently Used)**: Doubly Linked List + Hash Map forms the classic **O(1) cache**.
- **Music/Video Players**: Sequential playlists with prev/next navigation.
- **Polynomial Arithmetic**: Efficient insertion of terms in sorted order.
- **Operating Systems**: Process control blocks, thread scheduling lists.

> [!NOTE]
> **Engineering Fact:** The Linux kernel uses doubly linked lists extensively in its `list.h` header for managing task lists, device drivers, and memory pages.
