## 3. Step-by-Step Derivations — Algorithmic & Pointer-Logic Analysis

> [!NOTE]
> **Lab Context:** The "derivations" for a Data Structures Lab experiment are the **algorithmic derivations** — the careful, line-by-line derivation of pointer manipulations, complexity bounds, and execution flow. Every transition below is shown explicitly with the **Why** explained.

### 3.1 Algorithm Derivation: Insertion at the Beginning

**Problem Statement:** Given a `head` pointer to a (possibly empty) DLL, insert a new node containing value `x` as the **new first element**.

**Step-by-Step Pointer Logic Derivation:**

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Step 1:} \quad & \text{newNode} = (\text{Node}*) \text{malloc}(\text{sizeof(Node)}) \\
\text{Step 2:} \quad & \text{newNode->data} = x \\
\text{Step 3:} \quad & \text{newNode->prev} = \text{NULL} \quad \text{(it will be the new first node)} \\
\text{Step 4:} \quad & \text{newNode->next} = \text{head} \quad \text{(its next is the old head)} \\
\text{Step 5:} \quad & \text{If } \text{head} \neq \text{NULL}: \text{head->prev} = \text{newNode} \\
\text{Step 6:} \quad & \text{head} = \text{newNode}
\end{aligned}
$$

**Why each step matters:**
- Step 1: Dynamic allocation — DLL nodes do not exist until `malloc` succeeds.
- Step 3: First node's `prev` is always `NULL` by definition.
- Step 4: Must be done **before** updating `head`, otherwise we lose the old list.
- Step 5: Edge case — if the list is empty, there is no old head to update.
- Step 6: Anchor `head` to the new node — this makes the new node the official first node.

**Resulting C Function:**

```c
void insertAtBeginning(Node **head, int x) {
    Node *newNode = (Node *)malloc(sizeof(Node));
    newNode->data = x;
    newNode->prev = NULL;
    newNode->next = *head;
    if (*head != NULL)
        (*head)->prev = newNode;
    *head = newNode;
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Why `Node **head` (double pointer)?** Because we are modifying the caller's `head` pointer itself. A single pointer would only let us modify the *node* head points to, not the pointer itself.

### 3.2 Algorithm Derivation: Insertion at the End

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Step 1:} \quad & \text{newNode->data} = x, \quad \text{newNode->next} = \text{NULL} \\
\text{Step 2:} \quad & \text{If head} == \text{NULL}: \text{head} = \text{newNode}, \text{ return} \\
\text{Step 3:} \quad & \text{temp} = \text{head}; \quad \text{while (temp->next} \neq \text{NULL): temp} = \text{temp->next} \\
\text{Step 4:} \quad & \text{temp->next} = \text{newNode} \\
\text{Step 5:} \quad & \text{newNode->prev} = \text{temp}
\end{aligned}
$$

**C Implementation:**

```c
void insertAtEnd(Node **head, int x) {
    Node *newNode = (Node *)malloc(sizeof(Node));
    newNode->data = x;
    newNode->next = NULL;

    if (*head == NULL) {
        newNode->prev = NULL;
        *head = newNode;
        return;
    }

    Node *temp = *head;
    while (temp->next != NULL)
        temp = temp->next;

    temp->next = newNode;
    newNode->prev = temp;
}
```

### 3.3 Algorithm Derivation: Insertion at a Specific Position

Given position `pos` (1-indexed):

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Step 1:} \quad & \text{If pos} == 1: \text{call insertAtBeginning(), return} \\
\text{Step 2:} \quad & \text{newNode->data} = x; \quad \text{temp} = \text{head}; \quad i = 1 \\
\text{Step 3:} \quad & \text{While } i < pos - 1 \text{ AND temp} \neq \text{NULL}: temp = temp->next; i++ \\
\text{Step 4:} \quad & \text{If temp} == \text{NULL}: \text{print "Position out of range", free(newNode), return} \\
\text{Step 5:} \quad & \text{newNode->next} = temp->next} \\
\text{Step 6:} \quad & \text{If temp->next} \neq \text{NULL}: \text{temp->next->prev} = \text{newNode} \\
\text{Step 7:} \quad & \text{temp->next} = \text{newNode} \\
\text{Step 8:} \quad & \text{newNode->prev} = temp
\end{aligned}
$$

### 3.4 Algorithm Derivation: Deletion by Value (Key)

$$
\begin{aligned}
\text{Step 1:} \quad & \text{If head} == \text{NULL: print "List empty", return} \\
\text{Step 2:} \quad & \text{temp} = \text{head} \\
\text{Step 3:} \quad & \text{If temp->data} == \text{key}: \text{head} = \text{temp->next; if (head} \neq \text{NULL) head->prev} = \text{NULL; free(temp); return} \\
\text{Step 4:} \quad & \text{While temp} \neq \text{NULL AND temp->data} \neq \text{key: temp} = \text{temp->next} \\
\text{Step 5:} \quad & \text{If temp} == \text{NULL: print "Not found", return} \\
\text{Step 6:} \quad & \text{If temp->next} \neq \text{NULL: temp->next->prev} = \text{temp->prev} \\
\text{Step 7:} \quad & \text{temp->prev->next} = \text{temp->next} \\
\text{Step 8:} \quad & \text{free(temp)}
\end{aligned}
$$

### 3.5 Complexity Derivation Matrix

| Operation | Pointer Writes | Pointer Reads | Traversal Length | Big-O |
| :- | :- | :- | :- | :- |
| Insert Beginning | 4 | 1 | 0 | **O(1)** |
| Insert End | 2 | n + 1 | n | **O(n)** |
| Insert Position | 4 | 2(p−1) | p−1 | **O(n)** |
| Delete Beginning | 3 | 1 | 0 | **O(1)** |
| Delete End | 2 | n + 1 | n | **O(n)** |
| Delete by Key | 3 | 2k | k | **O(n)** |
| Reverse Traverse | 0 | n | n | **O(n)** |

Where `n` = list length, `p` = position, `k` = position of searched key.

### 3.6 Analytical "Spot the Bug" Matrix (Common Viva Traps)

> [!WARNING]
> **Top 5 DLL Programming Mistakes — Board Examiners Look for These:**

| # | Common Mistake | Symptom | Fix |
| :- | :- | :- | :- |
| 1 | Updating `head` before saving `head->next` | List lost after `insertAtBeginning` | Save `*head` in `newNode->next` **first** |
| 2 | Forgetting to update `prev` after `next` change | Unidirectional link — backward traversal crashes | Always set both `next` and `prev` |
| 3 | Not checking `head == NULL` before `head->prev` | Segmentation fault on empty list | Add `if (head != NULL)` guard |
| 4 | Using single pointer `head` instead of `&head` | Insertions at beginning don't reflect | Pass `Node **head` |
| 5 | Memory leak — not calling `free()` after `delete` | Valgrind reports leaked blocks | Always `free(deletedNode)` |

### 3.7 Complete Self-Contained C Program (Implementation Master)

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

typedef struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node *prev;
    struct Node *next;
} Node;

Node* createNode(int x) {
    Node *n = (Node *)malloc(sizeof(Node));
    n->data = x;
    n->prev = n->next = NULL;
    return n;
}

void insertBeginning(Node **head, int x) {
    Node *n = createNode(x);
    n->next = *head;
    if (*head) (*head)->prev = n;
    *head = n;
}

void insertEnd(Node **head, int x) {
    Node *n = createNode(x);
    if (!*head) { *head = n; return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    while (t->next) t = t->next;
    t->next = n;
    n->prev = t;
}

void insertAtPos(Node **head, int x, int pos) {
    if (pos == 1) { insertBeginning(head, x); return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    for (int i = 1; i < pos - 1 && t; i++) t = t->next;
    if (!t) { printf("Invalid position\n"); return; }
    Node *n = createNode(x);
    n->next = t->next;
    if (t->next) t->next->prev = n;
    t->next = n;
    n->prev = t;
}

void deleteBeginning(Node **head) {
    if (!*head) { printf("Empty list\n"); return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    *head = t->next;
    if (*head) (*head)->prev = NULL;
    free(t);
}

void deleteEnd(Node **head) {
    if (!*head) { printf("Empty list\n"); return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    if (!t->next) { *head = NULL; free(t); return; }
    while (t->next) t = t->next;
    t->prev->next = NULL;
    free(t);
}

void deleteKey(Node **head, int key) {
    if (!*head) { printf("Empty list\n"); return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    while (t && t->data != key) t = t->next;
    if (!t) { printf("Key not found\n"); return; }
    if (t->prev) t->prev->next = t->next; else *head = t->next;
    if (t->next) t->next->prev = t->prev;
    free(t);
}

void displayForward(Node *head) {
    printf("Forward: ");
    while (head) { printf("%d <-> ", head->data); head = head->next; }
    printf("NULL\n");
}

void displayBackward(Node *head) {
    if (!head) { printf("Backward: NULL\n"); return; }
    while (head->next) head = head->next;
    printf("Backward: ");
    while (head) { printf("%d <-> ", head->data); head = head->prev; }
    printf("NULL\n");
}

int main(void) {
    Node *head = NULL;
    insertEnd(&head, 10);
    insertEnd(&head, 20);
    insertBeginning(&head, 5);
    insertAtPos(&head, 15, 3);
    displayForward(head);
    displayBackward(head);
    deleteKey(&head, 15);
    displayForward(head);
    deleteBeginning(&head);
    deleteEnd(&head);
    displayForward(head);
    return 0;
}
```

