### 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

> **[KTU University Exam – Sample Paper 2024 Scheme]**

**Q1. Differentiate between a Singly Linked List (SLL) and a Doubly Linked List (DLL). Mention any two advantages of DLL over SLL.**
**[3 Marks | CO1, Bloom Level: Understand]**

**Model Answer:**

A **Singly Linked List** contains nodes with **one pointer** (`next`), allowing traversal in only one direction. A **Doubly Linked List** contains nodes with **two pointers** (`prev` and `next`), enabling bidirectional traversal.

Two advantages of DLL over SLL:

1. **Reverse Traversal:** DLL supports backward traversal from any node using `prev` pointers; SLL cannot traverse backwards without recursion or restructuring.
2. **O(1) Deletion Given a Node:** Given a node reference in DLL, deletion takes constant time because `node->prev` is directly available; SLL must traverse from `head` to find the predecessor, costing O(n).
3. **Insert Before a Given Node:** DLL can insert before a known node in O(1); SLL must traverse to the predecessor first.

