**Q2. Write the C structure definition for a node of a Doubly Linked List that stores an integer data value.**
**[3 Marks | CO1, Bloom Level: Remember]**

**Model Answer:**

```c
struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node *prev;
    struct Node *next;
};
typedef struct Node Node;
```

The `data` field holds the integer payload, `prev` stores the address of the previous node (or `NULL` if it is the first node), and `next` stores the address of the next node (or `NULL` if it is the last node).

