### 5.2 Part B Question A (14 Marks — Choice 1)

**[KTU University Exam – December 2023 Model | CO2, CO3 | Bloom Level: Apply / Analyze]**

**Q A(a). Write a C program to implement a Doubly Linked List with the following operations: (i) Insert at the beginning, (ii) Insert at the end, (iii) Delete from the beginning, (iv) Delete from the end. Provide a menu-driven main function and display the list after each operation.**
**[7 Marks]**

**Model Solution (Step-by-Step):**

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

typedef struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node *prev;
    struct Node *next;
} Node;

Node* createNode(int x) {
    Node *n = (Node *)malloc(sizeof(Node));
    n->data = x;
    n->prev = n->next = NULL;
    return n;
}

void insertBeginning(Node **head, int x) {
    Node *n = createNode(x);
    n->next = *head;
    if (*head) (*head)->prev = n;
    *head = n;
    printf("%d inserted at beginning\n", x);
}

void insertEnd(Node **head, int x) {
    Node *n = createNode(x);
    if (!*head) { *head = n; printf("%d inserted at end\n", x); return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    while (t->next) t = t->next;
    t->next = n;
    n->prev = t;
    printf("%d inserted at end\n", x);
}

void deleteBeginning(Node **head) {
    if (!*head) { printf("List empty\n"); return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    printf("%d deleted from beginning\n", t->data);
    *head = t->next;
    if (*head) (*head)->prev = NULL;
    free(t);
}

void deleteEnd(Node **head) {
    if (!*head) { printf("List empty\n"); return; }
    Node *t = *head;
    if (!t->next) { printf("%d deleted from end\n", t->data); free(t); *head = NULL; return; }
    while (t->next) t = t->next;
    printf("%d deleted from end\n", t->data);
    t->prev->next = NULL;
    free(t);
}

void display(Node *head) {
    printf("List: ");
    while (head) { printf("%d <-> ", head->data); head = head->next; }
    printf("NULL\n");
}

int main(void) {
    Node *head = NULL;
    int ch, x;
    while (1) {
        printf("\n1.InsertBeg 2.InsertEnd 3.DelBeg 4.DelEnd 5.Display 6.Exit\nChoice: ");
        scanf("%d", &ch);
        switch (ch) {
            case 1: scanf("%d", &x); insertBeginning(&head, x); display(head); break;
            case 2: scanf("%d", &x); insertEnd(&head, x); display(head); break;
            case 3: deleteBeginning(&head); display(head); break;
            case 4: deleteEnd(&head); display(head); break;
            case 5: display(head); break;
            case 6: return 0;
        }
    }
}
```

**Complexity Analysis:**

| Operation | Time | Justification |
| :- | :- | :- |
| Insert Beginning | **O(1)** | Only `head` rewire |
| Insert End | **O(n)** | Traverse whole list |
| Delete Beginning | **O(1)** | Just `head = head->next` |
| Delete End | **O(n)** | Reach last node |

