### 5.3 Part B Question B (14 Marks — Choice 2)

**[KTU University Exam – June 2024 Model | CO3, CO4 | Bloom Level: Analyze / Evaluate]**

**Q B(a). Write a C function to delete a node from a Doubly Linked List given the value (key) to be deleted. The function should correctly handle: (i) empty list, (ii) deleting the first node, (iii) deleting the last node, (iv) deleting a middle node, (v) key not found. After deletion, the list must remain a valid DLL.**
**[7 Marks]**

**Model Solution:**

```c
void deleteKey(Node **head, int key) {
    if (*head == NULL) {
        printf("List is empty\n");
        return;
    }

    Node *temp = *head;

    /* Traverse to find the node */
    while (temp != NULL && temp->data != key)
        temp = temp->next;

    if (temp == NULL) {
        printf("Key %d not found\n", key);
        return;
    }

    /* Case: temp is the first node */
    if (temp->prev == NULL) {
        *head = temp->next;
        if (*head != NULL) (*head)->prev = NULL;
    }
    /* Case: temp is the last node */
    else if (temp->next == NULL) {
        temp->prev->next = NULL;
    }
    /* Case: temp is a middle node */
    else {
        temp->prev->next = temp->next;
        temp->next->prev = temp->prev;
    }

    printf("Deleted %d\n", temp->data);
    free(temp);
}
```

**Edge Case Trace Summary:**

| Case | List State Before | List State After | Action |
| :- | :- | :- | :- |
| Empty | `NULL` | `NULL` | Print "List is empty" |
| First node | `5 <-> 10` (key=5) | `10` | `head = head->next; head->prev = NULL` |
| Last node | `5 <-> 10` (key=10) | `5` | `temp->prev->next = NULL` |
| Middle node | `5 <-> 10 <-> 15` (key=10) | `5 <-> 15` | Both `next` and `prev` rewire |
| Not found | `5 <-> 10` (key=99) | unchanged | Print "Not found" |

