### 5.4 Examiner's Valuation Warning — Where Students Lose Marks

> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Board Examiner Pitfall Callout — Top Reasons for Mark Deduction:**
>
> 1. **Forgetting to set `prev = NULL` in `createNode`:** Causes garbage `prev` pointers that crash backward traversal. **−1 mark**
> 2. **Passing `head` instead of `&head`:** Insert/deletion at beginning silently fails. **−2 marks**
> 3. **Missing `head == NULL` check before `head->prev`:** Segmentation fault on empty list — **zero output, full loss**. **−2 marks**
> 4. **Not freeing deleted nodes (memory leak):** Examiner runs Valgrind; leak = **−1 mark**
> 5. **Not handling `pos == 1` separately in `insertAtPos`:** Causes out-of-bounds or wrong insertion. **−1 mark**
> 6. **Off-by-one in traversal loop (`i < pos` vs `i < pos - 1`):** Position is interpreted incorrectly. **−1 mark**
> 7. **Failing to update BOTH `next` and `prev` after a deletion:** List becomes a "broken DLL" where backward traversal skips a node. **−2 marks**
> 8. **No menu-driven output in Part B questions:** Examiner expects interactive demonstration. **−1 mark**

